definitions.example: I expect it will set us back by a day or so, but I think a side trip will be worthwhile.

definitions.definition: To remove from or allow distance.
definitions.example: Set it back from the road by twenty or thirty feet.

definitions.definition: To install or position behind a boundary or surface, or in a recess.
definitions.example: The statue was set back in a niche.
How much do you suppose that fancy dress set her back?
